Your app is not serving with COOP and COEP headers.

As a result, window.crossOriginIsolated is false, and WebContainer initialization fails.

This behavior is expected when loading from platforms like Vercel or default local servers without COI headers.

üõ† How to resolve
If you're using Vite locally:
Install and configure vite-plugin-coi:

bash
Î≥µÏÇ¨
Ìé∏Ïßë
pnpm add vite-plugin-coi -D
Add it to your vite.config.ts:

ts
Î≥µÏÇ¨
Ìé∏Ïßë
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import { coiPlugin } from 'vite-plugin-coi';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react(), coiPlugin()],
});
This will automatically inject COOP/COEP headers for dev.

If your app is deployed on Vercel:
Set HTTP headers for cross-origin isolation using vercel.json:

json
Î≥µÏÇ¨
Ìé∏Ïßë
{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy",
          "value": "require-corp"
        },
        {
          "key": "Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy",
          "value": "same-origin"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
Or, if using Next.js, configure in next.config.js:

js
Î≥µÏÇ¨
Ìé∏Ïßë
module.exports = {
  async headers() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/(.*)',
        headers: [
          { key: 'Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy', value: 'require-corp' },
          { key: 'Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy', value: 'same-origin' }
        ]
      }
    ];
  }
};
