‚úÖ After making these changes:
Rebuild/re-deploy your site (pnpm dev or push to Vercel).

Confirm in browser console:

js
Î≥µÏÇ¨
Ìé∏Ïßë
console.log(window.crossOriginIsolated); // should now be true
The WebContainer should now initialize, and live preview inside the Sandbox node should work.

Why it matters
SharedArrayBuffer is disabled by default on major browsers unless your page is cross-origin isolated:

This prevents spectre/meltdown cross-origin attacks.

WebContainers need this for multi-threaded memory features to work.

Once isolation is enabled, WebContainer will start and your sandbox node can boot with fully isolated execution.

